Use double quotes for normal text:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    greeting = "Hello"
]

Expression-position backtick strings aren't implemented. Use an ordinary string
with escapes when the text contains backslashes:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    windows_path = "C:\\docs\\site"
]

Use single quotes for one character:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    seedling = '🌱'
]

Use a template when text needs values or a larger structure:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    name = "Ada"

    greeting = [:
        Hello, [name]
    ]
]

Square brackets belong to templates. Collections use curly braces instead.
